compareDesigns

public boolean compareDesigns(Design design1,
                              Design design2,
                              boolean verbose)
This method will compare two designs and optionally print the differences found. Unless the parameter verbose is specified, the method will return at the first sign of a difference.

Parameters:
design1 - First design to compare.
design2 - Second design to compare.
verbose - A flag which indicates to print all differences found between the two designs
Returns:
True if the designs are identical, false otherwise.
